name: FF 94
text: For fast pizza this place rocks! There have been a few times when I was caught last minute and needed a fair amount of food fast, if you call ahead you can get all of them ready before you arrive, and much faster then other pizza places. ‚Ä¶More

name: Brian Berend
text: Quick trip in and out. Made our pizzas fresh as it was a large order. Price was definitely right. Big hit with the kids after the golf tournament.

name: Lori Chilcutt
text: Good cheap pizza. Friendly workers.

name: Leta Manning
text: I would rather spend the extra money and go across the street than be treated poorly or see someone else treated poorly for placing a large order in person. The girl that worked tonight was out of line! üëéüèª

name: Tyler Davis
text: Please don't go here, the franchise owner yells and belittles their employees and the restaurant is far from sanitary. Prices keep going up now the once $5 pepperoni is now $7.99. the other local pizza restaurants I promise will give you what you pay for.

name: Brian Durnil
text: I'll never go there again! Their pepperoni pizza is $6.99 not the $5.99 as advertised and the quality isn't worth paying the extra money's! Hell for $1 more dollar u can go to dominos or Pizza Hut!
